com.github.methylene.lists

Class LookupList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • com.github.methylene.lists.LookupList<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>, RandomAccess
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ByteList, CharList, ComparableList, ComparatorList, DoubleList, FloatList, IntList, LongList, ShortList

    public abstract class LookupList<E>
extends AbstractList<E>
implements RandomAccess

    Base class for all List implementations in this package.

    LookupList is an immutable, null-rejecting, array based implementation of List that is optimized for search. Its indexOf, lastIndexOf and contains methods will often perform much better than those of other array based list implementations.

    LookupList implementations store a sorted array internally, so binary search can be used.

    Consequentially, the list can only contain things that can be compared: primitives or Comparables. Building a list from arbitrary objects is also possible if a suitable Comparator is provided.

    Instances of this list are slower to create and use more memory than ArrayList. For each element in the list, an extra 8 bytes (two ints) are needed to store its original position.

    The speedup of the search methods depends on the size of the list, and also on the cost of the equals method of its elements.

      • indexOf

        public abstract int[] indexOf(E el,
            int size)
        Find at most size indexes i where 
        
   this.get(i).equals(el)
        The returned array will always be sorted. For example, this method could be used to find duplicates in the list as follows: 
        
   public  E findDuplicate(LookupList list) {
     for (E el: list) {
       if (list.indexOf(el, 2).length == 2) {
         return el;
       }
     }
     return null;
   }
        If size < 0, all indexes are returned. If el is not in the list, this returns an empty array.
        Parameters:
        el - an object
        size - a number
        Returns:
        the array of all indexes where the value equals el
